pullRequest.body:
Define the notion of algebra of sets and prove basic properties.
Define the algebra of set generated by a family and prove basic properties.
Prove that the algebra of sets generated by a countable family is countable.

---

This is the first PR involving a whole new file that I do on my own, with new definitions and the use of namespaces. I tried to inspire from the similar files `PiSystem` and `SetSemiring`.

```suggestion
of sets is a family of sets containing the empty set and closed by complement and binary union.
```

I am not sure it is a good idea to use an implicit argument here, given how it forces you to use the `@` version everywhere below. Same thing for the other fields.

```suggestion
union of finite intersections of sets which are in `𝒜` or have their complement in `𝒜`. -/
```
